69.pdf","abstract":"An important theorem of Ling states that if $G$ is any factorizable non-fixing group of homeomorphisms of a paracompact space then its commutator subgroup $[G,G]$ is perfect. This paper is devoted to further studies on the algebraic structure (e.g. uniform perfectness, uniform simplicity) of $[G,G]$ and $[\\tilde G,\\tilde G]$, where $\\tilde G$ is the universal covering group of $G$. In particular, we prove that if $G$ is bounded factorizable non-fixing group of homeomorphisms then $[G,G]$ is uniformly perfect (Corollary 3.4). The case of open manifolds is also investigated. Examples of homeomorphism groups illustrating the results are given.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1016/J.TOPOL.2011.05.005","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-07-27T14:18:20.006Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"Z/HL2vMpTyiW3YqgNUslgA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"sX3Vm8oVTjqUJfuEeSZm/A==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"610015acd112b71809959a24"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"+wKZ28rTTN6e5Q/jkc2wDQ==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"A note on the volume flux group of four-manifolds","authors":["J. Petean","P. Suárez-Serrato"],"date":{"$date":"2010-07-27T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1016/J.TOPOL.2009.12.003","abstract":"Abstract We show that closed orientable smooth four-manifolds with non-trivial volume flux group and fundamental group of subexponential growth type are finitely covered by a manifold homeomorphic to S 3 × S 1 , S 2 × T 2 or a nil-manifold. We also show that if a compact complex surface has non-trivial volume flux group then it has zero minimal volume.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1016/J.TOPOL.2009.12.003","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-07-27T14:18:20.113Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"Z/HL2vMpTyiW3YqgNUslgA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"610015acd112b71809959a25"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"yl+p/Zy/SRG2pgGKO4RiyQ==","$