ilarity. Once this space has been produced, tasks such as face recognition, verification and clustering can be easily implemented using standard techniques with FaceNet embeddings asfeature vectors. Our method uses a deep convolutional network trained to directly optimize the embedding itself, rather than an intermediate bottleneck layer as in previous deep learning approaches. To train, we use triplets of roughly aligned matching / non-matching face patches generated using a novel online triplet mining method. The benefit of our approach is much greater representational efficiency: we achieve state-of-the-artface recognition performance using only 128-bytes perface. On the widely used Labeled Faces in the Wild (LFW) dataset, our system achieves a new record accuracy of 99.63%. On YouTube Faces DB it achieves 95.12%. Our system cuts the error rate in comparison to the best published result [15] by 30% on both datasets.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1109/CVPR.2015.7298682","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-01T09:52:53.110Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"0TJDQaGUTS+ftv0UNaxX6A==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"61066ef6ecc93e6fb1f6bfa9"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"sYftR39WTrOF7SuHhtlLkA==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"CraftAssist Instruction Parsing: Semantic Parsing for a Voxel-World Assistant","authors":["Kavya Srinet","Yacine Jernite","Jonathan Gray","Arthur D. Szlam"],"date":{"$date":"2020-08-01T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://www.aclweb.org/anthology/2020.acl-main.427.pdf","abstract":"We propose a semantic parsing dataset focused on instruction-driven communication with an agent in the game Minecraft. The dataset consists of 7K human utterances and their corresponding parses. Given proper world state, the parses can be interpreted and executed in game. We report the performance of baseline models, and analyze their successes and failures.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.18653/v1/2020.acl-main.427",