ebpage classification task, showing that accuracy can be significantly improved by modeling relational dependencies.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.5555/2073876.2073934","journal_title":null},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T08:39:59.046Z"},"cited_articles":[]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107d1d7942a4b6254576fef"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"3FFnQ8NBQgGeuRI8LN1nKg==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"On the structure of the group of Lipschitz homeomorphisms and its subgroups, II : Dedicated to Professor Hideki Imanishi on his 60th birthday","authors":["Kōjun Abe","K. Fukui"],"date":{"$date":"2003-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.2969/jmsj%2F1191418758","abstract":"Semantic Scholar extracted view of ","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.2969/jmsj/1191418758","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":true,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T11:07:03.929Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"sX3Vm8oVTjqUJfuEeSZm/A==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"lhrrh692RWq103stjJo/mQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"zemTqLjARiuxcfCpJLe4AA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"QOoswOTvRjCWY32xAREGig==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"hoxkig5bR0SHbI6onKWr3w==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"RGRVhAVzTfeSER4imgajJw==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"3OqwKmzQSnWuzWL31aSxZA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107d1d8942a4b6254576ff0"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"YP8A/QWoRPSQKhFMNXUr/w==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"On the structure of the group of equivariant diffeomorphisms","authors":["A. Banyaga"],"date":{"$date":"1977-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1016/0040-9383%2877%2990009-X","abstract":"We put on Di&‘(M) the C’-topology, and we denote by Diffd(M), the identity component in Diffd(M). If L is a subgroup of a group K, we shall denote by [L, K] the subgroup of K generated by commutators of elements of L and of K. The group [K, K] is called the commutator subgroup. We shall denote by H,(K) the abelianised group of K