 out. Experimental results show that Cloak reduces the mutual information between the input and the sifted representations by 85.01% with only negligible reduction in utility (1.42%). In addition, we show that Cloak greatly diminishes adversaries’ ability to learn and infer non-conducive features.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1145/3442381.3449965","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":true,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T11:22:00.883Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"is5Ld28hSMGZtIzAhHw/mA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107d558942a4b6254577005"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"ZUoxWxdBQ76wZXQoFj42gA==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Wherefore art thou R3579X?: anonymized social networks, hidden patterns, and structural steganography","authors":["L. Backstrom","C. Dwork","J. Kleinberg"],"date":{"$date":"2011-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2043199","abstract":"Semantic Scholar extracted view of ","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1145/2043174.2043199","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T11:22:00.971Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"dQ01eAbmQCOzw9UTJo5r8Q==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"6szprE7eRy2nB9WWCSQ/kA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"VvPRe9QeS/GeUg7DLVuPaA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"NA1NExzKSTG3MycxxTHXTg==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"RYameQnGTaWLx2vs/MJGtQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"xKpwZSKDQ4aWv1xVjqdmmQ==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107d559942a4b6254577006"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"+/RPEFLwRuSO2AsVQemGGg==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Multirelational k-Anonymity","authors":["M. Nergiz","Chris Clifton","A. Nergiz"],"date":{"$date":"2009-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1109/TKDE.2008.210","abstract":"k-anonymity protects privacy by ensuring that data cannot be linked to a single individual. In a k-anonymous data set, any identifying informa