a given by the users of an online service predict personal information of nonusers. Using data from a disappeared social networking site, we perform a historical audit to evaluate whether personal data of nonusers could have been predicted with the personal data and contact lists shared by the users of the site. We analyze personal information of sexual orientation and relationship status, which follow regular mixing patterns in the social network. Going back in time over the growth of the network, we measure predictor performance as a function of network size and tendency of users to disclose their contact lists. This article presents robust evidence supporting the shadow profile hypothesis and reveals a multiplicative effect of network size and disclosure tendencies that accelerates the performance of predictors. These results call for new privacy paradigms that take into account the fact that individual privacy decisions do not happen in isolation and are mediated by the decisions of others.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1126/sciadv.1701172","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":true,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T11:23:30.640Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"is5Ld28hSMGZtIzAhHw/mA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"6szprE7eRy2nB9WWCSQ/kA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"psqSUkC6SwC+cT1MMHLfzw==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"yJfe3NaLS1iuFthtKb6MzQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"QAbet1fWSmW19Sp22/IViQ==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107d5b3942a4b6254577073"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"fcDz2EDHRIeEGCLwndlqdg==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Detecting and preventing inference attacks in online social networks: A data-driven and holistic framework","authors":["X. He","Haibing Lu"],"date":{"$date":"2017-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1080/15536548.2017.1357383","abstract":"ABSTRACT With increasing user involvement, social networks nowadays serve as a repository of all kinds of information. While 