oretical models have not been shown to capture behavior in real-world social networks. Here, we introduce a richer model relating geography and social-network friendship, in which the probability of befriending a particular person is inversely proportional to the number of closer people. In a large social network, we show that one-third of the friendships are independent of geography and the remainder exhibit the proposed relationship. Further, we prove analytically that short chains can be discovered in every network exhibiting the relationship.</p>","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1073/pnas.0503018102","journal_title":"Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":true,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T12:00:55.915Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"PpegjJqGSCeoY+VddjuQ9g==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"is5Ld28hSMGZtIzAhHw/mA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"Wnnm/tTySqm8ekRNNMyXIg==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"lK6wjVugScyJw81o6nHKvQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"2fPH1lE4SuKTle7uFrq6OQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"8eC4MK1yRYW1783UGV/8XQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"xMPdG/7yQ7+zP22y51B6Vw==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"xDnflsLjTuOb+S/QNVPmrg==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"YvyjZ5C0TH+LluQGhlgyWA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"KXz3kwYfQ3+jYXwqD6s4NQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"RkKAEDQtSH6dsMRQVPyHvA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"RowoFXivR/u+jZW72jPk7g==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"+lCHCA0wS8C0/r/cZAAmaA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"hIHbAMGYQp+aI9nrFpS3SA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"Tr5H2XtOQTK2KNawEBvRUQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"Ru7XC1dMTmeQR6Xm9icBng==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"0okI9mjuSlmkOHWPY0Qjog==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"+OYh/atMRrSPHVAztcts+g==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"T8pMM6iGTCOT+lGZlNBkeA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"/WOSwfI7SuCUG+qBDGS6SQ==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"b9L+IbzNTgGVp2lp06XtjA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"JXqMKlMuQ/CF92R5sq5AYA==","$type":"4"},{"$binary":"f/Ben0S3T5SPwR3ymiOXmQ==","$type":"4"},{"$