 group of diffeomorphisms by a trajectory of minimal length. This shows the difficulty of applying the variational method to construct nonstationary flows in the 3-dimensional case.He shows that in the 3-dimensional case the group of diffeomorphisms has finite diameter, in contrast to the 2-dimensional case. He describes completion (as a metric space) of the group of volume-preserving diffeomorphisms of a 3-dimensional region; it consists of all measurable, not necessarily invertible volume-preserving maps of the region into itself.Bibliography: 6 titles.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1070/SM1987V056N01ABEH003025","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:20:26.052Z"},"cited_articles":[]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f11ab023a101bc07fc90"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"3JTZ94RvRLWfPF4cEn9sWA==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Complete metrics of bounded curvature on noncompact manifolds","authors":["R. Greene"],"date":{"$date":"1978-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01226419","abstract":"Semantic Scholar extracted view of ","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1007/BF01226419","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:20:26.166Z"},"cited_articles":[]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f11ab023a101bc07fc91"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"fmMd9RDtRtKdQv1M/VpGyw==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Generalized fluid flows, their approximation and applications","authors":["A. Shnirelman"],"date":{"$date":"1994-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01896409","abstract":"Semantic Scholar extracted view of ","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1007/BF01896409","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:20:26.281Z"},"cited_articles":[]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f11ab023a101bc0