017","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:25:02.010Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"C3tPDxiBQfWqJepaMpuwxA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f22fb023a101bc07fd36"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"rN/fFX9HSP6P8FFYO2fqxw==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Merging Observed and Self-Reported Behaviour in Agent-Based Simulation: A Case Study on Photovoltaic Adoption","authors":["Andrea Borghesi","M. Milano"],"date":{"$date":"2019-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.3390/APP9102098","abstract":"Semantic Scholar extracted view of ","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.3390/APP9102098","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:25:03.084Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"C3tPDxiBQfWqJepaMpuwxA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f230b023a101bc07fd37"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"ic1mkNxdQ9aHc3e0PHW2Jw==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"The Role of Clustering in the Adoption of Organic Dairy: A Longitudinal Networks Analysis between 2002 and 2015","authors":["J. C. S. Herrera","C. Dimitri"],"date":{"$date":"2019-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/a25c/e899555d886882ea7885531adf83adc4efa4.pdf","abstract":"This paper uses network analysis to study the geo-localization decisions of new organic dairy farm operations in the USA between 2002 and 2015. Given a dataset of organic dairy certifications we simulated spatio-temporal networks based on the location of existing and new organic dairy farming operations. The simulations were performed with different probabilities of connecting with existing or incoming organic farmer operations, to overcome the lack of data describing actual connections between farmers. Calculated network statistics on the simulated networks included the average degree, average shortest path, closeness (centralit