 the overlay with better routability observed from the first step, we propose and evaluate a social-based bootstrapping method for nodes to join the overlay, under the constraints imposed by firewalls and NATs. In our analysis, we consider both real and synthetic datasets of online social networks. The results of our evaluation show that structured P2P overlay routability is severely hampered by wide-scale partition events. In addition, the proposed social-based unstructured overlay network provides improved routability while maintaining a smaller number of links. Furthermore, in the evaluation of bootstrapping, by varying several input parameters, from 90 to 97 percent of nodes in Social-aware overlay could bootstrap and reach their direct-neighbors.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1109/TNSE.2018.2871980","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:25:06.887Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"C3tPDxiBQfWqJepaMpuwxA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f233b023a101bc07fd3f"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"2IbZOcXfQseqd6AujeaS6A==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"14. Network Analysis Links Parts to the Whole","authors":["F. Jordán"],"date":{"$date":"2019-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"https://doi.org/10.1525/9780520934313-016","abstract":"Semantic Scholar extracted view of ","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.1525/9780520934313-016","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:25:07.202Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"C3tPDxiBQfWqJepaMpuwxA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f233b023a101bc07fd40"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"O9uLLGYlSAusoiIuRKO9BQ==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Global air transport complex network: multi-scale analysis","authors":["Weisi Guo","Bogdan Toader","Roxana Feier","Guillem Mosquera","Fabian Ying","Sewook Oh","Matthew Price-Williams","Armin Krupp"],"d