hich is shown to reduce the time to search for information in networks. Our final strategy balances search times and participation costs and is shown to decrease time to find information in decentralized search in online social networks. Our strategy also balances strong-ties (within communities) and weak-ties over long distances (between communities that bring in diverse ideas) and may ultimately lead to more productive and innovative networks of human communication and enterprise. We hope that this work will lay the foundation for strategies aimed at producing global scale human interaction networks that are sustainable and lead to a more networked, diverse and prosperous society.","arxiv_id":null,"doi":"10.7906/indecs.14.1.2","journal_title":"undefined"},"created_by":null,"proposed_to":[],"related_articles_were_imported":false,"id":null,"created_at":{"$date":"2021-08-02T13:26:49.777Z"},"cited_articles":[{"$binary":"C3tPDxiBQfWqJepaMpuwxA==","$type":"4"}]},{"_id":{"$oid":"6107f299b023a101bc07fdbf"},"asset_id":{"$binary":"IexTDywORniqd1KcomP61g==","$type":"4"},"payload":{"title":"Socially aware integrated centralized infrastructure and opportunistic networking: a powerful content dissemination catalyst","authors":["Jie Hu","Lie-liang Yang","Kun Yang","L. Hanzo"],"date":{"$date":"2016-08-02T00:00:00.000Z"},"pdf_url":"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/stamp/stamp.jsp?tp=&arnumber=7537181","abstract":"The classic centralized infrastructure (CI) exhibits low efficiency in disseminating the content of common interest across its requesters. In order to overcome the limitations of CI-based content dissemination, smart mobile devices are capable of activating direct opportunistic communications among mobile users, which returns in integrated cellular and opportunistic networks. During the content dissemination process, the social characteristics of multiple users, including their common interest in the content, their mobility patterns, their social ties, and their altruistic forw